* Download <tt>clamav-0.90.2.tar.gz</tt> from http://www.clamav.net/download/sources
* Build:

<pre>tar xzvf clamav-0.90.2.tar.gz 
cd clamav-0.90.2
./configure --sysconfdir=/etc
make
make check</pre>

* Backup old configuration:

<pre>sudo cp /etc/freshclam.conf /etc/freshclam.conf.old
sudo cp /etc/clamd.conf /etc/clamd.conf.old</pre>

* Uninstall old version, install new version:

<pre>cd ../clamav-0.90.1
sudo make uninstall
cd ../clamav-0.90.2
sudo make install
sudo ldconfig -v</pre>

* Post install checks:

<pre>whereis freshclam
sudo freshclam -v
sudo service clamd restart
sudo service --status-all | grep clamd
cd /etc

# check config files for changes
diff freshclam.conf freshclam.conf.old
diff clamd.conf clamd.conf.old

# check startup script for changes
cd -
diff contrib/init/RedHat/clamd /etc/init.d/clamd</pre>

